Police on Wednesday found bhang worth Sh65,500 in an abandoned car in Rangwe, Homa Bay County.  The discovery was made after members of the public informed the police that the vehicle had been left unattended for hours at Ngegu market.  On inspection, the police officers found 605 rolls of bhang stashed in the boot of the Toyota Ipsum. The vehicle was towed to Homa Bay Police Station.  Confirming the incident, Homa Bay County Police Commander Esther Seroney said police are hunting for suspects who abandoned the car.  Seroney said the suspects may have abandoned it after one of its tyres developed a puncture.  MPs’ say on the hot bhang debate  Time will tell: Kenya Rastafarians’ quest for legalising marijuana  Bhang worth Sh4 million destroyed in Embu [VIDEO]  Suspect in Sh15m bhang case refuses to take plea “Concerned residents liaised with our officers who rushed to the scene and found the narcotics in the vehicle. Investigations are ongoing,” said Seroney.  The commander added that police are also looking for the owner of the Ipsum.      Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  Dr. Amolo who was stabbed by his son passes on  Suala la uvutaji bangi laleta changamoto kubwa kwa wenyeji wa Muranga  Polisi wanasa magunia 7 za bangi Voi katika barabara kuu ya Nairobi-Mombasa By Kepher Otieno | 2 hours ago By Winfrey Owino | 6 hours ago By Mate Tongola and Hamza Yusuf | 10 hours ago By Daniel Chege | 10 hours ago President Uhuru Kenyatta furious over recent string of losses